Process Engineer

Duracell US Operations Inc

- Fairburn, GA 30213

Summary
Duracell is an iconic brand and the world’s leading manufacturer of high performance alkaline batteries, power cells, and rechargeables. We are the most trusted source of personal power because of our sustained commitment to innovation, producing more compact, more powerful, and longer lasting batteries.
As a Process Engineer, you will be responsible for new initiative validation, material cost savings qualification/delivery, roll-out/reapplication package validation, and DuraLINK technology integration into the Packing operation.
As a Process Engineer, some of your essential duties and responsibilities may include:
Validate Process Control Strategies (PCS) for new equipment and formulation changes
Validate Centerline packages for new equipment and formulation changes
Lead manufacturing verification of new design innovation lead line/systems (SR/TR ownership)
Deliver Roll-out / Reapplication PCAs/PQs and manufacturing verification for new design innovations
Key Qualifications
You may fit well into this role if you:
Effectively develop procedures and technical documents
Design and execute experimental trial plans in a manufacturing environment (high speed assembly and batch process skills a plus)
Skill to analyze streams of process/vision system data and subsequently identify root cause and systemically eliminate manufacturing losses
Education & Experience
Please consider applying if you have:
A BS in Engineering Discipline or Engineering Technology equivalent experience (Electrical, Chemical, or Mechanical preferred)
2 – 3 years of experience in a manufacturing and/or R&D environment (consumer products a plus)
Experience in data analytics and reporting a plus
If you can imagine yourself in this role, we look forward to hearing from you. Duracell is committed to hiring incredible talent and, as such, offers competitive compensation packages and employee benefits. To this same end, Duracell respects and values the aspects that make each candidate unique and, as an Equal Opportunity employer, is committed to providing a work environment that is free of discrimination against employees and applicants on the basis of any factor prohibited by applicable laws and regulations.
